JS was originally created as an addition to 
netscape, a web browser that existed before
firefox. IN 1995, netscape hired Bandon Eich
to create a new programming language to beforeembedded into the
Navigator--this became Javascript

1996--Javascript submitted to international
students body, ECMA international

1997--first official specification released
under the name ECMAscript

Techincally, JS is considered as an implementation
of ECMAScript- more or less synonymous

ES6 contains many improvements

Vanilla Javascript refers to the core JS
technologies without use of additional
technologies (w/o frameworks & libraries)